gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"6663f46a963778aa0753cf5f985306b8bfd6522a","tid":2394887,"uid":51271,"like":18,"dislike":0,"score":18,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-04T13:35:31.000Z","msg":"我搵咗美國加洲幼稚園課程簡介，無劉副校長所講嘅&quot;國家安全&quot;，佢老吹<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.dmusd.org/cms/lib02/CA01001898/Centricity/Domain/59/kindercurriculum.pdf\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dmusd.org%2Fcms%2Flib02%2FCA01001898%2FCentricity%2FDomain%2F59%2Fkindercurriculum.pdf&d=LTOHNK%2B9fuVs8qin7tjZRH88up93QrsUiEJqOxYGoBw%3D&h=ba09b5b4\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.dmusd.org/cms/lib02/CA01001898/Centricity/Domain/59/kindercurriculum.pdf</a><br />\n<br />\nNational and State Symbols <br />\n<br />\n<br />\nKindergarten students explore the strands of national identity and cultural literacy by learning about national and state symbols. <strong>Students should learn to recognize national and state symbols such as the national and state flags, the bald eagle, and the Statue of Liberty and how these symbols relate to America&rsquo;s cultural and national identity. Students can discuss the values and principles in these symbols, such as individual rights, common good, justice, equality, and truth. </strong><br />\n<br />\nThe teacher may choose to integrate this standard with Standards K.6.1 and K.6.2 and create a larger unit on national symbols, holidays, and important Americans. Literature&mdash;such as Fireworks, Picnics, and Flags (James Giblin) and Purple Mountain Majesties (Barbara Younger)&mdash;can both engage and develop student understanding of these standards. <br />\n<br />\nIn addition, songs such as Woody Guthrie&rsquo;s &ldquo;This Land Is Your Land,&rdquo; &ldquo;America the Beautiful,&rdquo; and the &ldquo;Star-Spangled Banner&rdquo; all support student engagement and learning."},{"pid":"fcb33881132a511e3e367105e1f1994c2ec180ca","tid":2394887,"uid":64072,"like":15,"dislike":0,"score":15,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2